1. Waiver. To the extent possible under law, the Affirmer expressly waives all of his or her rights to the work, whether known or unknown, including but not limited to all copyright and related or neighboring rights, in the work.

2. Public License Fallback. If the Affirmer is unable to waive all of his or her rights to the work, then the Affirmer grants to anyone the right to use the work for any purpose, without any conditions, unless such conditions are required by law.

3. No Warranties. The Affirmer makes no representations or warranties about the work, and disclaims all liability related to the work to the fullest extent permitted by applicable law.

